1}$ respectively, outperforming CCSD(T):UHF by nearly a factor of 5.\nMoreover, the performance on the closed- and open-shell subsets show these\nmethods are able to treat open-shell and closed-shell systems with comparable\naccuracy and robustness. The use of $\\kappa$-OOMP2 orbitals has also proven\nuseful in diagnosing multireference character that can hinder the reliability\nof CCSD(T).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Jul 2020 16:23:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 17 Jul 2020 02:06:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-19"}
